Package: scimesh
Type: Package
Title: Headless 3D Mesh Rendering Engine
Version: 0.2.4
Authors@R: c(
    person("Tim", "Schaefer", email = "ts+code@rcmd.org",
           role = c("aut", "cre"))
    )
Description: A fast, GPU-free 3D software rasterizer written in modern C++17 with
    native R bindings. Renders triangle meshes to publication-quality images
    entirely on the CPU, requiring no OpenGL, GPU, or display server.
    Features multi-light Blinn-Phong shading, screen-space ambient occlusion,
    anti-aliasing, depth cueing, transparency, wireframe rendering, texture
    mapping, and procedural geometry generation. Supports STL, OBJ, and PLY
    mesh formats with PNG, PPM, and BMP output. Works on HPC clusters,
    headless servers, containers, and CI pipelines, making it suitable for
    scientific visualization across neuroimaging, molecular structures, and
    general 3D graphics.
